.SS Record Configuration Options 
This section describes the options used for the recording
features.
.PP
To start the recording press \(oqleft_ctrl+enter\(cq. To end the
recording and to save the clip press \(oqenter\(cq. If you press the
start key more than one time the recording starts from the
last press.
.SS record_sound 
Enables or disables the sound recording.
.PP
record_sound yes | no
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
.PP
The sound clip is saved in the \(oqdir_snap\(cq directory (like the
snapshot images) in \(oq.wav\(cq format. Specifically the \(oqWAV PCM
16 bit\(cq format is used. The sample rate used is the same sample
rate specified with the \(oqsound_samplerate\(cq option.
.PP
The clip is saved without compression and without any volume
adjustment. You should use an external utility to adjust the
volume and compress the resulting file.
.SS record_video 
Enables or disables the video recording.
.PP
record_video yes | no
.PD 0
.PP
.PD
.PP
The video clip is saved in the \(oqdir_snap\(cq directory (like the
snapshot images) in \(oq.mng\(cq format. The \(oqMNG\(hyLC\(cq (Low Complexity)
subformat is used.
.PP
The clip is saved with a lite compression, you should use an
external utility to compress better the resulting file.
.PP
A powerful compression utility is the \(oqadvmng\(cq program
available in the AdvanceCOMP package.
.SS record_video/sound_time 
Controls the maximum length in seconds of the recording feature.
.PP
